background:#fef3c7;color:#d97706;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:9999px;\">MODERATE</span></td><td style=\"padding:7px 10px;font-size:11px;color:#6b7280;\">Elevated P/E; Q2 earnings Aug 4 is next binary event (8+ weeks)</td></tr>\n  </table>\n  <p style=\"margin:6px 0 20px;color:#9ca3af;font-size:10px;\">All five positions MODERATE (31&#8211;50). No HIGH or EXTREME flags. Semi concentration at 80.4% &#8212; noted but not a forced rotation trigger.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#ffffff;padding:0 32px;\"><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;margin:0;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- WHAT TO DO THIS WEEKEND -->\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#ffffff;padding:20px 32px 24px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;color:#111827;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;\">What to Do This Weekend / Monday Open</p>\n  <table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:5px 0;color:#374151;font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#ea580c;\">&#128276; LLY + TSM:</strong> Decide on the TP1 trims this weekend. Both clear the commission rule but barely. If you trust TP2 for both, holding is rational. If you want locked gains, execute. Don't overthink it &#8212; the thesis on both is unchanged.</td></tr>\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:5px 0;color:#374151;font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#059669;\">&#10003; AMD:</strong> No action. Watch Monday &#8212; a close above entry ($428.84) is the confirmation signal. Below entry still = recovery phase, not breakout. TP1 at $493 (+17%) is the first real objective if it clears entry.</td></tr>\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:5px 0;color:#374151;font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#374151;\">&#128202; AVGO:</strong> Hold. Post-earnings digestion takes 2&#8211;4 weeks. Q3 guide $29.4B (AI tripling to $16B) hasn't been walked back. TP1 at $474 (+13.2%) is the line to watch.</td></tr>\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:5px 0;color:#374151;font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#374151;\">&#128202; NVDA:</strong> Stable near entry through AVGO contagion. Q2 FY27 earnings ~Aug 2026 is the next catalyst. Nothing to do.</td></tr>\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:5px 0;color:#374151;font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;\"><strong style=\"color:#374151;\">&#128197; Jun 11:</strong> TSM ex-dividend date ($0.955/ADR). Your 0.224 shares earns ~$0.21.</td></tr>\n  </table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr><td style=\"background-color:#ffffff;padding:0 32px;\"><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;margin:0;\"></td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION MODULE -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:24px 32px;background-color:#eff6ff;border-radius:0 0 12px 12px;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#1e40af;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;\">&#128218; Today&#8217;s Equity Concept</p>\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 14px;color:#1e3a8a;font-size:15px;font-weight:800;\">Earnings Whisper Numbers &#8212; AVGO Gave You a Live Masterclass</p>\n  <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;color:#1e3a8a;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;\">Published sellside consensus (Bloomberg, FactSet) is the floor &#8212; it&#8217;s what gets printed in the headlines. The whisper number is what the buyside is <em>actually</em> pricing in, and it&#8217;s almost always higher. AVGO on June 3: consensus was $2.40 EPS. They printed $2.44 &#8212; a technical beat. AI revenue doubled. Q3 guide $29.4B was formally above street estimates. And the stock dropped 13%. Why? The buyside whisper had two additional conditions: (1) Hock Tan raises the $100B full-year AI target, and (2) confirms the integrated AI systems strategy. He delivered neither. The headline reads &#8220;AVGO beats&#8221; &#8212; the market heard &#8220;guidance unchanged, strategy backpedalled.&#8221; Beat the number, missed the expectations around the number. For AMD&#8217;s August 4 print: check whether buyside whispers are running 10&#8211;15% above the published EPS estimate. If they are, AMD needs to beat the whisper magnitude, not just clear the bar.</p>\n  <p style=\"margin:0;color:#3b82f6;font-size:11px;font-style:italic;\"><strong>Also today:</strong> <em>Options-implied move</em> &#8212; before AVGO&#8217;s print, options were pricing in ~9% either way. It moved 13%. Realized volatility exceeded implied volatility. That&#8217;s why selling options before binary events is dangerous even when IV looks expensive.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"padding:14px 32px;background-color:#f4f5f7;\">\n  <p style=\"margin:0;color:#9ca3af;font-size:10px;line-height:1.5;\">Research output only &#8212; not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Halal compliance verified via Musaffa (AAOIFI) as of 11 May 2026 &#8212; reverify quarterly. Price sources: Yahoo Finance, CNBC, MarketBeat via web search. &#9888; = June 4 confirmed close; &#10003; = June 5 confirmed close. Verify prices in your broker before executing. Generated 5 June 2026, 11:05 PM Kuwait Time (AST, UTC+3).</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>"
